  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group cooperation\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Report (SAR) reporting mandates\n\n3. Key Legal Provisions\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Establishing reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Defining predicate offenses\n- Implementing transaction monitoring systems\n- Establishing penalties and sanctions\n\n4. Compliance Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment procedures\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Regular reporting to financial regulators\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Asset seizure\n- Financial penalties\n- International cooperation in investigations\n\n6. Emerging Areas\n- Cryptocurrency regulations\n- Digital transaction monitoring\n- Cross-border regulatory coordination\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.",
